  "texts": [
    "A TiN BE was formed via the same HfSiO x -based SRM fabrication method to prepare a memristor without selection functionality.",
    "Subsequently, a 4-nm-thick GeTe thin film was deposited on the electrode as the active layer using a radio frequency (RF) magnetron sputtering system.",
    "A TE pattern was formed using photolithography, and a 200nm-thick Cu layer was deposited over these layers using DC magnetron sputtering.",
    "After the final liftoff process, a Cu/GeTe/TiN-stacked memristor device was successfully fabricated.",
    "A customized CA switching zig, CA probe station, and CA probe card were used to access individual cells in the CA and characterize the CA devices."
  ],
